%F A390029 Let F(t,n,k) be a 2k-order central finite difference of power t^(2n): F(t,n,k) = Sum_{j=0..2k} (-1)^j * binomial(2k,j) * (t+k-j)^(2n). Then:
%F A390029 T(n,k) = F(2, n, k).
%e A390029 Triangle begins:
%e A390029   k=      0       1         2           3         4           5          6
%e A390029   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%e A390029   n=0:    1;
%e A390029   n=1:    4,      2;
%e A390029   n=2:   16,     50,       24;
%e A390029   n=3:   64,    602,     1560,       720;
%e A390029   n=4:  256,   6050,    40824,     90720,     40320;
%e A390029   n=5: 1024,  57002,   818520,   4339440,   8467200,    3628800;
%e A390029   n=6: 4096, 523250, 14676024, 151367040, 663949440, 1157587200, 479001600;
%e A390029   ...
%t A390029 T[t_, n_, k_] := Sum[(-1)^j * Binomial[2 k, j]* (t + k - j)^(2 n), {j, 0, 2 k}];Table[T[2, n, k], {n, 0, 10}, {k, 0, n}] // Flatten
